    "created_at": "2017-05-10T11:03:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-05-10T11:04:20Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "#11190 and this are separate both in terms of implementation and in whether or not we want to implement them, so It would be better to keep the two discussions separate IMO.\r\n\r\nFor this one, I don't see any strong arguments for keeping identical AI behaviour on restart.  The way to fix it is to change [HackyAI.cs#L345](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/bleed/OpenRA.Mods.Common/AI/HackyAI.cs#L345) to be seeded with something that is different each invokation.  `CosmeticRandom` is one such source (`SharedRandom` won't work, because that needs to be synced across all players), or the current time is another."
